#, no-c-format
msgid "Output: <computeroutput>&#x1234;</computeroutput>"
msgstr "Resultado: <computeroutput>&#x1234;</computeroutput>"

#. Tag: primary
#: advanced.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid "replace, sed style"
msgstr "Substitución estilo sed"

#. Tag: secondary
#: advanced.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "search, sed style"
msgstr "Busca estilo sed"

#. Tag: term
#: advanced.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>s///[ig]</command> <command>%s///[ig]</command>"
msgstr "<command>s///[ig]</command> <command>%s///[ig]</command>"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This command does a sed-like search/replace operation on the current line, "
"or on the whole file (<command>%s///</command>)."
msgstr ""
"Busca ou substitución de estilo sed na liña actual, ou en todo o ficheiro "
"(<command>%s///</command>)."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:433
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In short, the text is searched for text matching the <emphasis>search "
#| "pattern</emphasis>, the regular expression between the first and the "
#| "second slash, and when a match is found, the matching part of the text is "
#| "replaced with the expression between the middle and last part of the "
#| "string. Parentheses in the search pattern create <emphasis>back "
#| "references</emphasis>, that is the command remembers which part of the "
#| "match matched in the parentheses; these strings can be reused in the "
#| "replace pattern, referred to as <userinput>\\1</userinput> for the first "
#| "set of parentheses, <userinput>\\2</userinput> for the second and so on."
msgid ""
"In short, the text is searched for text matching the <emphasis>search "
"pattern</emphasis>, the regular expression between the first and the second "
"slash, and when a match is found, the matching part of the text is replaced "
"with the expression between the second and last slash. Parentheses in the "
"search pattern create <emphasis>back references</emphasis>, that is the "
"command remembers which part of the string matched in the parentheses; these "
"strings can be reused in the replace pattern, referred to as <userinput>\\1</"
"userinput> for the first set of parentheses, <userinput>\\2</userinput> for "
"the second and so on."
msgstr ""
"En resumo, búscase texto que coincida co <emphasis>patrón de busca</"
"emphasis> (a expresión regular entre a primeira e a segunda barra), e cando "
"se atope unha coincidencia, esta substituirase polo texto entre a segunda e "
"a terceira barra. Os parénteses no patrón de busca crean "
"<emphasis>referencias</emphasis>; é dicir, a parte da coincidencia que estea "
"entre parénteses poderá volver usarse no texto de substitución. Empregue "
"<userinput>\\1</userinput> para empregar o contido dos primeiros parénteses "
"no texto de substitución, <userinput>\\2</userinput> para o segundo par de "
"parénteses, etc."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To search for a literal <literal>(</literal> or <literal>)</literal>, you "
"need to <emphasis>escape</emphasis> it using a backslash character: "
"<userinput>\\(\\)</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Para incluír parénteses no patrón de busca e que estes teñan que coincidir "
"con parénteses no texto atopado en vez de crear referencias, debe "
"<emphasis>escapalos</emphasis> prefixándoos cunha barra: <userinput>\\(\\)</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you put an <userinput>i</userinput> at the end of the expression, the "
"matching will be case insensitive. If you put a <userinput>g</userinput> at "
"the end, all occurrences of the pattern will be replaced, otherwise only the "
"first occurrence is replaced."
msgstr ""
"Se pon un <userinput>i</userinput> ao final da expresión, a busca non "
"distinguirá entre maiúsculas e minúsculas. Se pon un <userinput>g</"
"userinput>, substituiranse todas as coincidencias co padrón —en caso "
"contrario só se fará unha substitución por liña—."

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replacing text in the current line"
msgstr "Substitución de texto na liña actual"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your friendly compiler just stopped, telling you that the class "
"<classname>myClass</classname> mentioned in line 3902 in your source file is "
"not defined."
msgstr ""
"O compilador detívose, e di que a clase <classname>unhaClase</classname> "
"mencionada na liña 3902 do ficheiro de código fonte non está definida."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&quot;Buckle!&quot; you think, it is of course <classname>MyClass</"
"classname>. You go to line 3902, and instead of trying to find the word in "
"the text, you launch the Editing Command Dialog, enter <userinput>s/myclass/"
"MyClass/i</userinput>, hit the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button, save the "
"file and compile &ndash; successfully without the error."
msgstr ""
"E de seguida lle chega a iluminación: «Claro! O nome correcto é "
"<classname>UnhaClase</classname>». Vai á liña 3902, e en vez de intentar "
"atopar a palabra no texto, inicia o diálogo de orde de edición, insire "
"<userinput>s/unhaclase/UnhaClase/i</userinput>, preme Intro, garda o "
"ficheiro e volve lanzar o compilador: «correctamente sen o erro»."

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:471
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replacing text in the whole file"
msgstr "Substitución de texto en todo o ficheiro"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine that you have a file, in which you mention a <quote>Miss Jensen</"
"quote> several times, when someone comes in and tells you that she just got "
"married to <quote>Mr Jones</quote>. You want, of course, to replace each and "
"every occurrence of <quote>Miss Jensen</quote> with <quote>Ms Jones</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Imaxine que ten un ficheiro no que menciona a <quote>Helena</quote> varias "
"veces, e vai alguén e lle di que a muller cambiou o nome, e agora se chama "
"<quote>Iria</quote>. En canto sae do teu asombro, decátase de que lle vai "
"tocar substituír todas as aparicións do nome no documento."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter the command line and issue the command <userinput>%s/Miss Jensen/Ms "
"Jones/</userinput> and hit return, you are done."
msgstr ""
"Acceda á liña de ordes e emita a orde <userinput>%s/Dona Helena/Dona Iria/</"
"userinput>, prema Intro, e listo."

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:486
#, no-c-format
msgid "A More Advanced Example"
msgstr "Un exemplo máis avanzado"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example makes use of <emphasis>back references</emphasis> as well as a "
"<emphasis>character class</emphasis> (if you do not know what that is, "
"please refer to the related documentation mentioned below)."
msgstr ""
"O seguinte exemplo usa <emphasis>referencias</emphasis> así como unha "
"<emphasis>clase de caracteres</emphasis> (máis adiante explicarase en que "
"consiste isto)."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suppose you have the following line:"
msgstr "Supoña que ten a seguinte liña:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: advanced.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"void MyClass::DoStringOps( String      &amp;foo, String &amp;bar, String *p, "
"int  &amp;a, int &amp;b )"
msgstr ""
"void UnhaClase::FacerCousas( String      &amp;isto, String &amp;estoutro, "
"String *p, int  &amp;a, int &amp;b )"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you realize that this is not nice code, and decide that you want to use "
"the <constant>const</constant> keyword for all <quote>address of</quote> "
"arguments, those characterized by the &amp; operator in front of the "
"argument name. You would also like to simplify the white space, so that "
"there is only 1 whitespace character between each word."
msgstr ""
"E de súpeto decátase de que este código é incorrecto de todo, e decide usar "
"a palabra clave <constant>const</constant> para todos os parámetros de "
"<quote>enderezos</quote>, aqueles cuxo nome vai precedido do operador &amp;. "
"Tamén lle gustaría simplificar os espazos, de xeito que só quede un entre "
"cada palabra."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Launch the Editing Command Dialog, and enter: <userinput>s/\\s+(\\w+)\\s"
"+(&amp;)/ const \\1 \\2/g</userinput> and hit the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> "
"button. The <userinput>g</userinput> at the end of the expression makes the "
"regular expression recompile for each match to save the "
"<emphasis>backreferences</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Inicie o diálogo de ordes de edición, insira <userinput>s/\\s+(\\w+)\\s"
"+(&amp;)/ const \\1 \\2/g</userinput> e prema Intro. O <userinput>g</"
"userinput> ao final da expresión fará que a expresión regular se volva "
"compilar para cada coincidencia, para así gardar as <emphasis>referencias</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Output: <computeroutput>void MyClass::DoStringOps( const String &amp;foo, "
"const String &amp;bar, String *p, const int &amp;a, const int &amp;b )</"
"computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"Resultado: <computeroutput>void UnhaClase::FacerCousas( const String &amp;"
"isto, const String &amp;estoutro, String *p, const int &amp;a, const int "
"&amp;b )</computeroutput>"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:513
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mission completed! Now, what happened? Well, we looked for some white space "
"(<literal>\\s+</literal>) followed by one or more alphabetic characters "
"(<literal>\\w+</literal>) followed by some more whitespace (<literal>\\s+</"
"literal>) followed by an ampersand, and in the process saved the alphabetic "
"chunk and the ampersand for reuse in the replace operation. Then we replaced "
"the matching part of our line with one whitespace followed by <quote>const</"
"quote> followed by one whitespace followed by our saved alphabetical chunk "
"(<literal>\\1</literal>) followed by one whitespace followed by our saved "
"ampersand (<literal>\\2</literal>)"
msgstr ""
"Conseguido! Pero que ocorreu? Pois ben, buscamos espazos (<literal>\\s+</"
"literal>) seguidos dun ou máis caracteres latinos de palabras (<literal>\\w"
"+</literal>) seguidos de máis espazos (<literal>\\s+</literal>) seguidos dun "
"«&amp;», e de paso gardamos os caracteres e o «&amp;» para volver usalos no "
"texto de substitución. A continuación substituímos a parte da liña que "
"coincide cun espazo, seguido de <quote>const</quote>, un espazo, a palabra "
"gardada (<literal>\\1</literal>), e o «&amp;» gardado (<literal>\\2</"
"literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now in some cases the alphabetical chunk was <quote>String</quote>, in some "
"<quote>int</quote>, so using the character class <literal>\\w</literal> and "
"the <literal>+</literal> quantifier proved a valuable asset."
msgstr ""
"Nalgúns casos a palabra gardada foi <quote>String</quote>, noutros "
"<quote>int</quote>, así que fixemos ben en usar a clase de caracteres "
"<literal>\\w</literal> e o cuantificador <literal>+</literal>."

