#~ msgid "Translation"
#~ msgstr "Internacionalización"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "In order to support full localization, there are several functions to "
#~ "translate strings in scripts, namely <literal>i18n</literal>, "
#~ "<literal>i18nc</literal>, <literal>i18np</literal> and <literal>i18ncp</"
#~ "literal>. These functions behave exactly like <ulink url=\"http://"
#~ "techbase.kde.org/Development/Tutorials/Localization/i18n\"> KDE's "
#~ "translation functions</ulink>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Para permitir a localización dos scripts, existen diversas funcións: "
#~ "<literal>i18n</literal>, <literal>i18nc</literal>, <literal>i18np</"
#~ "literal> and <literal>i18ncp</literal>. Estas funcións compórtanse "
#~ "exactamente como as <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde.org/Development/"
#~ "Tutorials/Localization/i18n\">funcións de internacionalización de KDE</"
#~ "ulink>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The translation functions translate the wrapped strings through KDE's "
#~ "translation system to the language used in the application. Strings in "
#~ "scripts being developed in the official &kappname; sources are "
#~ "automatically extracted and translatable. In other words, as a &kappname; "
#~ "developer you do not have to bother with message extraction and "
#~ "translation. However, for 3rd-party scripts developed outside of KDE, you "
#~ "have to extract and translate the messages yourself. Along with your "
#~ "scripts you have to also distribute a translation catalog, that includes "
#~ "all translated strings. Further, your script header then must explicitly "
#~ "state the catalog to load by specifying <literal>i18n-catalog</literal>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "As funcións de internacionalización utilizan o sistema de tradución de "
#~ "KDE para fornecer a versión das cadeas na lingua na que se executa o "
#~ "aplicativo. As cadeas dos scripts desenvolvidos na versión oficial de "
#~ "&kappname; extráense de maneira automática e póñense a disposición dos "
#~ "tradutores. É dicir, os desenvolvedores de &kappname; non teñen que "
#~ "preocuparse das extracción das mensaxes nin da súa tradución. Porén, no "
#~ "caso dos scripts de terceiros desenvolvidos fóra do paraugas de KDE, "
#~ "deberá extraer e traducir vostede mesmo as mensaxes. Ademais, a cabeceira "
#~ "do seu script deberá indicar o nome do catálogo coas mensaxes traducidas "
#~ "mediante a entrada <literal>i18n-catalog</literal>."

