#~ "this script."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<literal>type</literal> (obrigatorio). O valor deste campo, o tipo de "
#~ "script, debe ser <quote><literal>commands</literal></quote>. En caso "
#~ "contrario, &kappname; ignorará o script."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The scripting API presented here is available in all scripts, i.e. "
#~ "indentation scripts and command line commands. Before the contents of a "
#~ "script is loaded, &kappname; first adds several prototypes and functions "
#~ "to the scripting context. This convenience API contains prototypes like "
#~ "text cursors and text ranges and is located in the folder <filename>"
#~ "$KDEDIR/share/apps/katepart/api</filename>. There, the file names of each "
#~ "JavaScript file conforms with the following naming scheme: "
#~ "<programlisting>\n"
#~ "&lt;number&gt;_&lt;name&gt;.js\n"
#~ "</programlisting> The number has two digits and the name is an arbitrary "
#~ "name such as <quote><filename>myutils</filename></quote>. Through the "
#~ "number &kappname; controls the execution order of the API. I.e., the file "
#~ "called <filename>05_cursor.js</filename> is called before the file "
#~ "<filename>10_range.js</filename>. (This is similar to the start order of "
#~ "the runlevel/init system in Linux)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "A seguinte API para script está dispoñíbel para todos os scripts, "
#~ "independentemente do seu tipo (de sangrado ou da liña de ordes). Antes de "
#~ "cargarse o contido do script, &kappname; engade varios prototipos e "
#~ "funcións ao ambiente de execución. Esta API contén prototipos como "
#~ "cursores de texto e intervalos de texto, e está situada no cartafol "
#~ "<filename>$KDEDIR/share/apps/katepart/api</filename>. Nese cartafol, o "
#~ "nome de cada un dos ficheiros JavaScript segue o seguinte esquema:"
#~ "<programlisting>\n"
#~ "&lt;número&gt;_&lt;nome&gt;.js\n"
#~ "</programlisting> O número ten dúas cifras, e o nome pode ser un nome "
#~ "calquera, como por exemplo <quote><filename>ferramentas</filename></"
#~ "quote>. O número emprégao &kappname; para controlar a orde de execución "
#~ "da API. É dicir, o ficheiro <filename>05_cursor.js</filename> execútase "
#~ "antes que o ficheiro <filename>10_range.js</filename>."

